rn-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2530946\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 06, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104pjq1665702723793.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/pjq1665702723793.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/pjq1665702723793.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"pjq1665702723793\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body taskbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Each UST identifies a specific Uniface Server configuration. It can be defined in the assignment file of the Uniface Router, or it can be provided to the Uniface Router by a Uniface Server that has been started manually.\n </p>\n<section><ol class=\"ol steps\"><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"pjq1665702723793__li_d15731e1_d15732e1_d15733e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"pjq1665702723793__p_d30821e1_d30822e1_d30823e1\">Create an assignment file for each Uniface Server\n               to contain default paths for locating databases, files, and components. </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<p class=\"p\">For example, for a Uniface Server that has the UST (Uniface Server name)\n                     <code class=\"ph codeph\">Sales</code>, you could create <span class=\"ph filepath\">sales.asn</span>:</p>\n<div class=\"zDocsCodeExplanationContainer\"><button aria-label=\"Explain this code\" class=\"zDocsAiActionsButton\" data-target=\"#zDocsCodeExplanationModal_uniface_104pjq1665702723793_html_0\" data-toggle=\"modal\" tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-code-explanation\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-code-explanation\"></use></svg>Explain this code</button></div><div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre codeblock language-plaintext\" data-explanation-rendered=\"true\" id=\"pjq1665702723793__codeblock_nkf_gzr_gwb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">;sales.asn\n[PATHS]\n$DATA = MSS:DB:MAIN|user|pass\n\n[ENTITIES]\n*.* = $DATA:*.*</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"pjq1665702723793__li_d15734e1_d15735e1_d15736e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"pjq1665702723793__p_d30824e1_d30825e1_d30826e1\">Define the UST in the [SERVERS] section of the\n               Uniface Router's assignment file. </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<p class=\"p\">For example:</p>\n<div class=\"zDocsCodeExplanationContainer\"><button aria-label=\"Explain this code\" class=\"zDocsAiActionsButton\" data-target=\"#zDocsCodeExplanationModal_uniface_104pjq1665702723793_html_1\" data-toggle=\"modal\" tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-code-explanation\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-code-explanation\"></use></svg>Explain this code</button></div><div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre codeblock language-plaintext\" data-explanation-rendered=\"true\" id=\"pjq1665702723793__codeblock_nzw_hzr_gwb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">[SERVERS]\nSales= userver.exe /asn=sales.asn /maxidle=120 \nHR=userver.exe /asn=hr.asn</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"pjq1665702723793__li_d15737e1_d15738e1_d15739e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"pjq1665702723793__p_d30827e1_d30828e1_d30829e1\">If you start a Uniface Server manually (instead\n               of having the Uniface Router do it), specify the UST on the command line using the\n                  <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/ust</span> switch. </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<p class=\"p\">For example:</p>\n<div class=\"zDocsCodeExplanationContainer\"><button aria-label=\"Explain this code\" class=\"zDocsAiActionsButton\" data-target=\"#zDocsCodeExplanationModal_uniface_104pjq1665702723793_html_2\" data-toggle=\"modal\" tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-code-explanation\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-code-explanation\"></use></svg>Explain this code</button></div><div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre codeblock language-plaintext\" data-explanation-rendered=\"true\" id=\"pjq1665702723793__codeblock_xhz_3zr_gwb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">userver.exe /asn=sales.asn /dnp=TCP:ahost+13002 /ust=Sales</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</div>\n</li></ol></section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/xrd1665702718309.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>urouter.asn</a><p>Assignment file for the Uniface Router. You can use the urouter.asn file to specify settings, paths to connectors, and Uniface Server environment definitions, such as USTs.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/etu1665702548823.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>/ust</a><p>Register a client application or Uniface Server under a symbolic name with a Uniface Router.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ncb1665702745127.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Configuring the Uniface Server</a><p>You need to configure the Uniface Server so that it can find the databases and Uniface files, entities, and components that it needs.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2530946\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2530946\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Define Uniface Server Types (USTs) Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 06, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Each UST identifies a specific Uniface Server configuration. It can be defined in the assignment file of the Uniface Router, or it can be provided to the Uniface Router by a Uniface Server that has been started manually. Create an assignment file for each Uniface Server to contain default paths for locating databases, files, and components. For example, for a Uniface Server that has the UST (Uniface Server name) Sales , you could create sales.asn : Explain this code ;sales.asn [PATHS] $DATA = MSS:DB:MAIN|user|pass [ENTITIES] *.* = $DATA:*.* Copy Define the UST in the [SERVERS] section of the Uniface Router's assignment file. For example: Explain this code [SERVERS] Sales= userver.exe /asn=sales.asn /maxidle=120 HR=userver.exe /asn=hr.asn Copy If you start a Uniface Server manually (instead of having the Uniface Router do it), specify the UST on the command line using the /ust switch. For example: Explain this code userver.exe /asn=sales.asn /dnp=TCP:ahost+13002 /ust=Sales Copy Related Links urouter.asn Assignment file for the Uniface Router. You can use the urouter.asn file to specify settings, paths to connectors, and Uniface Server environment definitions, such as USTs. /ust Register a client application or Uniface Server under a symbolic name with a Uniface Router. Configuring the Uniface Server You need to configure the Uniface Server so that it can find the databases and Uniface files, entities, and components that it needs. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}